  "description": "Continuing on from my last babble, I\u0026rsquo;d like to think about the different kinds of encoding I\u0026rsquo;m working on - but not without a tip-of-the-hat toward overcoding.\nIf I try and just babble on it, a big part of what I\u0026rsquo;m trying to do is, under it, overcode the universe, so that each node of relational dynamics has a way to be encoded, fingerprinted, etc.\nWhile I recognize that\u0026rsquo;s an unrealistic goal, it\u0026rsquo;s the method that interests me: starting from the existing mapped network of relations and differentiating new relations by describing their differences.\n",
  "name": "2025-07-24, On encoding relational dynamics in gnoponemacs",
